reviewText:
This is a game I aways want to play, but never had a chance (I don't have a PSP and my notebook use Linux Mint). Now, thanks to Spike Chunsoft and Abstraction Games, I am blessed with this opportunity. And you know what? Now I now how gorgeous this game is. Let's talk about the good points of the game:

*Works smoothly on Linux+OpenGL;
*Game mechanic strangely works better on a pc than with a console;
*No problem with lost of quality on the game...instead it's difficult to look and see some aliasing;
*Great soundtrack (can't stop hearing Heat Up!);
*Great story (I catch some cases on the anime and never found out the game as so more rich in details, like interactions with your comrades);

I finish the chapter 2 right now, and I'm very anxious to play even more!
